{"word":"αὐτάρκης","slug":"αὐτάρκης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>αὐτάρϰης, ες</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:αὐτός\">αὐτός</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀρκέω\">ἀρκέω</a></el>] <b><i>satisfied/content, self-sufficient/independent,</i></b> either pair of glosses captures Paul’s interest in not being an economic burden to others <b><a href='B:570 4:11'>Phil 4:11</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:αὐτάρκεια\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:αὐτοκατάκριτος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}